-- 2012-03-05T21:43:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/kansas-oklahoma-wheat-ratings-fall-usda-says-texas-gains.html
About 50 percent of the winter-wheat
crop in  Kansas , the biggest grower, was in good or excellent
condition as of yesterday, down from 52 percent a week  earlier ,
the U.S. Department of Agriculture said.  In  Oklahoma , 62 percent of the winter wheat got the top
ratings, down from 67 percent the previous  week , the USDAâ€™s
 National Agricultural Statistics Service  said today on its
website. In  Texas , 33 percent of the winter wheat received the
top ratings, improving from 31 percent a week  earlier , the USDA
